>
  <h2>The question</h2>
  <p>Can a vision language model be built from the ground up with a focus on data efficiency rather than just raw scale?</p>

  <h2>What I built</h2>
  <p>A multimodal transformer architecture combining a ViT encoder with a decoder only language model. During development, I identified and fixed a causal masking bug that was causing the model to copy input tokens instead of predicting the next one.</p>

  <h2>What I found</h2>
  <p>Data quality and the parameter to token ratio are more critical than raw parameter count. Even a smaller model can outperform larger ones if the alignment phase is handled with high-signal data.</p>
</ProjectLayout>